 use of DMA buffers, adapters, and map registers.","pos":[5751,5821]},{"content":"Force IRQL checking","pos":[5828,5847]},{"content":"When this option is active, Driver Verifier places extreme memory pressure on the driver by invalidating pageable code.","pos":[5922,6041]},{"content":"If the driver attempts to access paged memory at the wrong IRQL or while holding a spin lock, Driver Verifier detects this behavior.","pos":[6042,6174]},{"content":"I/O verification","pos":[6181,6197]},{"content":"When this option is active, Driver Verifier allocates the driver's Interrupt Request Packets (IRPs) from a special pool, and monitors the driver's I/O handling.","pos":[6272,6432]},{"content":"This detects illegal or inconsistent use of I/O routines.","pos":[6433,6490]},{"content":"Driver Verifier also monitors the calls of several I/O Manager routines and performs stress testing of Plug-and-Play (PnP) IRPs, power IRPs and WMI IRPs.","pos":[6491,6644]},{"content":"Miscellaneous checks","pos":[6651,6671]},{"content":"When this option is active, Driver Verifier looks for common causes of driver crashes, such as the mishandling of freed memory.","pos":[6746,6873]},{"content":"Pool tracking","pos":[6880,6893]},{"content":"When this option is active, Driver Verifier checks to see whether the driver has freed all of its memory allocations when it is unloaded.","pos":[6968,7105]},{"content":"This reveals memory leaks.","pos":[7106,7132]},{"content":"Security checks","pos":[7139,7154]},{"content":"When this option is active, Driver Verifier looks for common errors that can result in security vulnerabilities, such as a reference to user-mode addresses by kernel-mode routines.","pos":[7229,7409]},{"content":"Special pool checking","pos":[7416,7437]},{"content":"When this option is active, Driver Verifier allocates most of the driver's memory requests from a special pool.","pos":[7512,7623]},{"content":"This special pool is monitored for memory overruns, memory underruns, and memory tha